# KIS-Points Architectural Rules

You are an expert developer helping to refactor KIS-Points to match the "Visual North Star" architecture. Always follow this structure:

## 1. Directory Structure
- /src/api: Shared Supabase DB logic (Point adding/deducting).
- /src/components/ui: Atomic Design blocks (Buttons, Badges, Cards).
- /src/components/features: Route-domain feature UIs (e.g. dashboard, landing, login, signup) composed from /ui and shared parts.
- /src/hooks: Custom React hooks (logic only).
- /src/layouts: Master screen layouts (e.g., Dashboard Sidebar/Frame).
- /src/lib: Shared utilities (Supabase client, TypeScript types).
- /src/pages: Route-specific screen views.
- /src/app: Next.js routing shells only.

## 2. Refactoring Principles
- "Bridge & Burn": Duplicate components to the new structure, update imports, then delete the old.
- "Logic Separation": Keep JSX in /pages, state in /hooks, and DB calls in /api.
- "Unified UI": Use the shared Atoms in /components/ui to ensure a consistent ecosystem.